name: Macon County Public Health (NC)
tweet: FACT: COVID-19 Vaccines protect against severe  symptoms, hospitalization, and even death associated with COVID-19 infections.   Getting vaccinated helps protect you and your community against the Delta Variant and keeps other Variants from coming into Macon County.  https://t.co/tAtGsL4aqF

name: Macon County Public Health (NC)
tweet: MCPH will be holding a Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine clinic on May 26th, 2021 from 2pm to 6pm. Those who are 12 years old or older are eligible to receive the vaccination. If you would like your child to be vaccinated, please call 828-524-1500 to schedule an appointment.  https://t.co/1bDFRjOB4x
